<br>
For very easy fights that still needs a placement of the mob is Cazic Thule. Our guild is fighting him near the little house and the tree where our healers move inside the house and the maintank back up against the tree so he wont be thrown away, and still be in range for CHs. <br>
<br>
If the gap between the maintank and the tree is to big, even tho the melees are evenly spread around the mob, i can send in my pet (that i parked behind CT) and with the help from a fellow mage i can push CT to his spot.<br>
<br>
If CT is to close to the tree, all i do is reposition the pet and call for mage assistance again, and do you know what, CT has stepped back and is on his right spot again.<br>
<br>
