<br>
It seems a lot of you guys use your pet on raid situations. How many people in tier 4 guilds use their pets? I don't. I don't think I am a lazy mage, I constantly debuff, DS tank group, rod ppl, summon focus items, all that good stuff. But it seems to me to just not be mana efficient in the slightest to use a pet. Examples:<br>
<br>
My guild has been doing the rings in PoE a LOT recently. Normal yard trash hits in the 800 range. Air pet has what, 3500 hp? That's 5 swings or so? Dead pet. Pet eats a few ripostes, and I am one second slow on enrage and boom, dead pet. Pullers get 2 inc, and mob decides to have my pet for lunch he does so in 4 seconds, then rips me a new one. Boo. Tried using a pet on Rallos Zek. Pet was dead almost as soon as I engaged. It just seems too much hassle to reposition pets behind mobs so not to eat ripostes and rage, constantly watch for adds, all the things I gotta do to keep ole Jabober alive. I feel like I'm doing more for the raid devoting my time to malosinia and nuking every mob once. (I'd nuke more but damn my guild has some DPS and the mobs die before I could land a second)<br>
<br>
Does anyone else have these issues? I haven't used a pet in a couple weeks to be honest and I don't think any less of myself for not doing it. XP groups are way different, pet does a ton don't get me wrong I use pet there all the time. But high end raids...pets just die. A lot. And easily. Frankly I think even our resident Bst quit using his pet. I'm glad I'm not a necro, going thru 40 dots a night does not appeal to me in the slightest. Anyway, sorry to derail but this popped in my head as lots of you seem to use pets on raids, but are they up against mobs that break the 1k hit barrier??<br>
<br>
Baervon<br>
Arch Mage of Explicit<br>
Quellious server<br>
