<br>
I have to play my pet as a tank, that is not the ma, so when the ma backs up, I back my pet up, just like I would, if I was a tank and did not want to get the ma mad at me.  What would a raid say to a tank who kept pushing a mob, after the ma backed up, nothing good, I suspect.<br>
<br>
I also play the caster role at the same time, I debuff the mob, hopefully I have already Ds'd the tank, if someone needs a rod, it is alot easier now with the /rt command to target the last person that sends you a tell, then Nuke in between all this, but not to much, so you don't take agro from your MA.<br>
<br>
During all this, you have to keep an eye on your second character, pet/tank.  Some people have a harder time than others on controling more than one character, so they choose not to have the pet, and maybe another class would be better for them.<br>
<br>
Just remember, you are not playing just one class, you are playing two at once with a pet.  You have to control your tank and be a caster at the same time. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Times New roman;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Gandolph / Kozymo</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
