Khan of the Dia Bakkus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=woonx>woonx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 374<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/03 4:56:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8974.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet usage and push</span><hr size=1> I do use pet pretty much 99,9% of the time, no reason not to with suspend 2 and pet hold AAs. Also I have insanely high resists (wich means my pet does too) so it's very rare that I'll have pet die on me. I used pet on every AD, RZ, TZ, etc mentioned in this thread and very rarely do I have my pet dying. Then again my 250+ all saves 300+ mr self buffed does help, pet hold, pet lay hand and suspend also rule for pet control.<br>
<br>
Like cyrius mentioned, making a habit of hitting pet hold (or pet back off if you don't have pet hold, but pet hold really is better/safer) before the mob enrage (mob will enrage as soon as they &quot;tick&quot; to 9% or below) will pretty much make sure pet almost never dies to rage.<br>
<br>
By not makin a pet, you cut your own damage output by at least 50 dps (and that's being conservative), and honestly, imho, with pet hold and suspend, there's no reason not to have a pet up at all time.<br>
<br>
Moral of the story, get pet hold and suspend, makes managing a pet a breeze. Back pet off when close to 10% on the mob. Always have your pet on /pet hold when not figthting, will prevent him running to the monks to see what just AoEed him. Pay attention to pet position and mob position, and you should be fine using a pet pretty much everywhere. Oh ya, NEVER CAN GET ENOUGH RESISTS! <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&lt;TDE&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
