<br>
2 things are really needed.  Pet suspend v2 .. and Pet hold . With those you should always have a pet up and out.  Only time my pet dies is when I am in mid cast and the monster hits the 10% marker, hot keys dont work when casting.  Having a fully buffed, equiped and suspended pet  helps a lot as you can spit it out if something goes wrong or your current one dies somehow.<br>
<br>
<br>
For those who have never been to plane of water.. here is a description by a guildie that is pretty accurate...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> I'm sure most of you out there have some fond memories of both Mistmoore and Kedge, right? Nights spent there, watching NPCs run/swim in the completely wrong directions, training you, people drowning, etc. The Plane of Water combines the charming qualities of both of those zones, together with 1k+ hitters and AEs that would make Sylvester Stallone cry. On top of the difficulties of fighting underwater, you've also got the lovely problem of the zone giving you the impression that the pathing was designed by a programmer who followed these steps:<br>
<br>
1. Dip ferret in paint. <br>
2. Wielding paint-covered ferret, flail wildly at a wall for five minutes. <br>
3. Take picture of wall. <br>
4. Scan picture into pathing database. <br>
5. Let cocaine-crazed chimpanzee play with the keyboard for a while. <br>
<br>
NPCs swim up. NPCs swim down. NPCs path completely around the zone, bringing back ten or fifteen playmates. NPCs sit motionless twenty feet away, in the middle of a swarm of other NPCs. NPCs randomly summon tanks to zone in. It's a joy. You'll love it once you experience it for yourself.<br>
</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
